## Session [2026-06-13] — Phase 4: Rust LLM Proxy + Sidecar Manager + Frontend Integration

### Phase 3 Deferred
- Phase 3 (Desktop Awareness) marked as OPTIONAL/DEFERRED to v0.1+
- Updated `phase-3.md`, `detailed_plan`, and roadmap to reflect deferral

### Rust Backend: LLM Proxy (`src-tauri/src/llm.rs`)
- Implemented streaming HTTP client for 5 LLM providers:
  - **Ollama**: POST /api/chat with SSE streaming
  - **OpenAI**: POST /v1/chat/completions with SSE streaming
  - **Anthropic**: POST /v1/messages with SSE streaming (event-based)
  - **Gemini**: POST /v1beta/models/{model}:streamGenerateContent
  - **DeepSeek**: OpenAI-compatible API
- Shared SSE parser handles all OpenAI-compatible providers
- Token-by-token emission via `llm:token` events
- `llm:done` and `llm:error` event signals
- Cancellation via `CancelMap` (std::sync::Mutex + HashMap)
- Cancellation checked between chunks for responsive stop

### Rust Backend: Sidecar Manager (`src-tauri/src/sidecar.rs`)
- JSONL IPC protocol over stdin/stdout for Python CSM process
- Streaming PCM audio chunk reception → `audio:chunk` events (base64 f32)
- Heartbeat health check every 5 seconds
- Process crash detection and status events (`sidecar:status`)
- `send_tts` command for sending text to CSM
- `kill` command for graceful shutdown

### Rust Backend: Tauri Commands (`src-tauri/src/lib.rs`)
- `send_chat_message` — spawns async LLM streaming, sends full response to TTS on completion
- `stop_generation` — sets cancellation flag for active request
- `start_sidecar` — spawns Python CSM process
- `check_sidecar_health` — returns running status
- `stop_sidecar` — kills sidecar process
- `send_tts` — sends text to sidecar for TTS generation
- State management via `AppState` with `CancelMap` + `Arc<SidecarProcess>`
- Window positioned at bottom-right of screen on startup

### New Rust Dependencies
- `reqwest = "0.12"` (features: stream, json) — HTTP client
- `uuid = "1"` (features: v4) — request IDs
- `futures-util = "0.3"` — stream combinators
- `base64 = "0.22"` — PCM audio encoding
- `bytes = "1"` — byte buffer utilities
- `tokio` (process, io-util, sync, time) — async runtime

### Frontend: API Layer (`src/lib/api.ts`)
- Tauri command wrappers: `sendChatMessage`, `stopGeneration`, `startSidecar`, `checkSidecarHealth`, `sendTts`
- Event listener helpers: `onLlmToken`, `onLlmDone`, `onLlmError`, `onAudioChunk`, `onAudioDone`, `onSidecarStatus`
- TypeScript interfaces matching Rust payload types

### Frontend: Audio Player (`src/lib/audio.ts`)
- `AudioPlayer` class using Web Audio API
- Base64 PCM → Float32Array → AudioBuffer → GainNode → Destination
- Progressive queue-based playback (plays next chunk when current ends)
- `stop()` and `clear()` for cancellation
- Singleton `audioPlayer` export

### Frontend: Store Updates
- **chat.ts**: Added `pendingRequests` (request_id → message_id mapping), `appendToMessage` for streaming token accumulation, `registerRequest` / `getMessageIdForRequest` for event-to-message routing
- **ChatInput.tsx**: Replaced simulated 1.5s timeout with real `sendChatMessage` Tauri command call
- **App.tsx**: Event listeners for `llm:token`, `llm:done`, `llm:error`, `audio:chunk`, `audio:done`, `sidecar:status`

